<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=At_the_Mountains_of_Madness&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Footnotes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Footnotes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small references-column-count references-column-count-2" style="-moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> S. T. Joshi, <i>The Annotated Lovecraft</i>, p. 175.</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Joshi and Schultz, p. 132.</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> Joshi, p. 18.</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> H. P. Lovecraft, <i>Selected Letters</i> Vol. 3, p. 144; cited in Joshi, p. 183; see also Joshi, p. 186.</li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> Lin Carter, <i>Lovecraft: A Look Behind the Cthulhu Mythos</i>, p. 84. Joshi regards this suggestion as "facile" - <i>Annotated Lovecraft</i>, pp. 17-18.</li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> H. P. Lovecraft, letter to August Derleth, May 16, 1931; cited in Joshi, pp. 329-330.</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> William Fulwiler, "E.R.B. and H.P.L.", <i>Black Forbidden Things</i>, p. 64.</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> H. P. Lovecraft, <i>Selected Letters</i> Vol. III, p. 186; Joshi, p. 175.</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> Joshi and Schultz, pp. 10-11.</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> H. P. Lovecraft, "<i>The Nameless City</i>", <i>Dagon and Other Macabre Tales</i>, pp. 104-105; cited in Joshi, pp. 264-265.</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> Lovecraft, <i>At the Mountains of Madness</i>, p. 4.</li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> H. P. Lovecraft, <i>Selected Letters</i> Vol. V, p. 228; Joshi, p. 181.</li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> Jason Colavito, <i>The Cthulhu Comparison</i></li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> Anthony Pearsall, <i>The Lovecraft Lexicon</i>, p. 326.</li>
<li id="cite_note-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14" title="">^</a></b> Ibid, p. 146.</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> Guillermo Del Toro Films, <a href="http://www.deltorofilms.com/ProjectPage.php?projectid=9" class="external text" title="http://www.deltorofilms.com/ProjectPage.php?projectid=9" rel="nofollow"><i>At the Mountains of Madness</i></a></li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.cthulhulives.org" class="external text" title="http://www.cthulhulives.org" rel="nofollow">"HPLHS"</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
